				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$s_t$$\end{document}st, who are not infected but can get infected when they come in contact with infected individuals.
Infected but undetected individuals, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$u_t$$\end{document}ut, who can infect susceptible individuals when they come in contact with them.
Infected individuals who test positive, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$p_t$$\end{document}pt.
Individuals who became COVID-19 positive but ultimately recovered from it, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
