We are able to study the effects of several refinements through agent-based simulations that do not appear in our analytical model. For example, in one of our experiments, we consider two different risk-groups within the population, one with a higher risk of infection transmission due to higher contact rates than another. Other example deviations from the analytical setup includes modeling the effect of delay \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
